    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-09-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="348"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <head>No. 348.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Nelson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-09-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 14, 1872</date>. (Received September
                        30.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 635.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 633, of yesterday, I have the
                    honor to inclose a translation of a note just received from Mr. Lafragua, in
                    reply to mine of the 4th instant, upon the complaints of the American colonists
                    at Tuxpan.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>THOMAS H. NELSON.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lafragua</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Nelson</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of Foreign Affairs</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-09-12">
                                <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 12, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your excellency’s note and
                        annexed document of the 4th instant, concerning the American colony at
                        Tuxpan, and have the honor to state that I have transmitted copies to the
                        treasury department, in order that, after inquiry, a proper determination
                        may be taken.</p>
                    <p>I take pleasure in renewing to your excellency the assurance of my high
                        consideration.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>J. M. LAFRAGUA.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
